****SPOILERS ARE INCLUDED IN THIS REVIEW****

Exactly how I imagined Daredevil. Great cast, great acting, great show. The distribution between time and back-stories of the main character and the villain is fair, so you get a good grip on the characters' previous life and their personal hardships and struggles. In fact, that having been said, every character has a back-story which gives you much more contact and passion for each character. i.e :

**SPOILER ALERT**

When Fisk kills his dad, you actually get a sense of sorrow for him and wonder if he really is the bad guy, after being so mistreated and abused.

Excited to watch Season 2, and I strongly recommend this show. It is definitely the highlight of Netflix.